issing Functionalities**: Implement the missing functionalities in `solution.py`. Ensure that your additions are compliant with the task description and requirements.\n\n4. **Revise the Code**: After adding the missing functionalities, revise the code to ensure it adheres to best practices, is well-documented, and is maintainable.\n\n5. **Call the `give_advice_and_revise` Action**: Once you have added and revised the code, call the `give_advice_and_revise` action to get feedback and further revisions.\n\n6. **Hand Over for Optimization**: After you have completed the above steps, you can let Agent 3 take over to optimize the code further.\n\nHere is an example of how you might structure your next task in terms of code changes:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n\n# Existing code (if any)\n\n# Add code coverage integration\ndef integrate_code_coverage():\n    # Implementation for code coverage\n    pass\n\n# Add complexity visualization\ndef visualize_complexity():\n    # Implementation for complexity visualization\n    pass\n\n# Add size estimation\ndef estimate_size():\n    # Implementation for size estimation\n    pass\n\n# Add real-time insights and recommendations\ndef provide_real_time_insights():\n    # Implementation for real-time insights and recommendations\n    pass\n\n# Main function to integrate all functionalities\ndef main():\n    integrate_code_coverage()\n    visualize_complexity()\n    estimate_size()\n    provide_real_time_insights()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    main()\n```\n\nAfter implementing the above changes, you should call the `give_advice_and_revise` action to get feedback and further improvements.', 'agent3': 'Given your role as a Senior Software Developer specialized in Python development, with a focus on fixing existing issues and optimizing code, the next logical step would be to start with the optimization phase of the MACAO system. Since you cannot create the code framework from scratch, you should focus on revising and optimizing the existing code.\n\nHere\'s a suggested next task:\n\n### Next Task: Optimize the Code\n\n**Objective:** Optimize the existing code in `solution.py` to improve its quality, coverage, complexity, and size estimation functionalities.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Analyze the Existing Code:**\n   - Review the current implementation in `solution.py`.\n   - Identify areas that can be improved in terms of performance, readability, and maintainability.\n\n2. **Code Coverage:**\n   - Ensure that the code has comprehensive test cases.\n   - Use tools like `coverage.py` to measure code coverage and identify untested parts.\n   - Write additional test cases to cover the untested parts.\n\n3. **Complexity Visualization:**\n   - Use tools like `radon` or `pylint` to analyze code complexity.\n   - Refactor complex functions or modules to make them more readable and maintainable.\n   - Visualize the complexity using tools like `pylint` reports or `radon` reports.\n\n4. **Size Estimation:**\n   - Implement or integrate a size estimation functionality.\n   - Use tools like `sloccount` or `cloc` to estimate the size of the project.\n   - Ensure that the size estimation is accurate and provides meaningful insights.\n\n5. **Real-time Insights and Recommendations:**\n   - Implement real-time monitoring and feedback mechanisms.\n   - Use web frameworks like Flask or Django to create a web interface for the MACAO system.\n   - Integrate tools like `Flask-SocketIO` for real-time updates.\n\n6. **Collaborative Platform:**\n   - Ensure that the system supports multiple developers.\n   - Implement features like version control integration, code review tools, and collaboration dashboards.\n\n7. **Documentation:**\n   - Document the code and the system architecture.\n   - Write user guides and developer documentation.\n\n**Action to Take:**\n- Call the `give_advice_and_revise` action to provide advice on the code and make necessary revisions.\n\n### Example Action Call:\n```json\n{\n  "type": "action_func